The leafy Durban neighbourhood has been beset by crime after a spate of brutal home invasions in recent weeks.Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said that while police were on patrol they spotted a suspicious vehicle ."Yesterday Westville police were doing their normal patrol duties when they spotted a suspicious vehicle with three occupants " he said."The suspects saw the police and opened fire while attempting to flee the scene."Zwane said that the policemen returned fire successfully bringing the car to a halt and wounding one of the gunmen."One suspect was wounded and the other two suspects were arrested at the scene for attempted murder and possession of an unlicensed firearm."He said that housebreaking implements and a firearm was recovered. - TMG Digital/The Times